  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Conflict Management and Reinforcement of Agro-Pastoral Resilience at the Mauritania - Mali Border</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project addresses the increase of conflicts identified on both sides of the Mauritanian-Malian border between pastoral, agro-pastoral and farmer communities located along the transhumance corridor. This programming involves the local communities present in this region in an effort to prevent and manage these conflicts. The goal is to reinforce the awareness and exchanges, as well as the overall vigilance of these communities, including structuring and training to better prevent and manage conflicts. This is done in collaboration with authorities, who are also supported in strengthening the collection and analysis of transhumance data. This data not only improves analyzes of the evolution of transhumance but also builds early warning mechanisms on the conflicts that take place between herders and farmers. IOM also works with herders in order to strengthen their resilience and improve their access to natural resources, while respecting local development conditions with the aim of improving coexistence and understanding between communities on both sides of the border. This enhanced resilience reduces the risk of conflict and strengthens cohesion between communities.</narrative>
  </description>
